    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-07T19:07:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-07T19:07:00-05:00" n="500"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">414.608/7–754: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Certain
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Offices</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d500fn1">Drafted by Deputy Assistant Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_WRF1">Woodward</persName>, with the assistance of Mr.
                            <persName corresp="#p_OJL1">Ohmans</persName>; approved by Assistant
                        Secretary <persName corresp="#p_HHF1">Holland</persName>. Sent to the
                        Embassies in Athens, Belgrade, Brussels, Copenhagen, <gloss
                            target="#t_HICOG1">HICOG</gloss> Bonn, Helsinki, Lisbon, Madrid, Oslo,
                        Paris, Rome, The Hague, Stockholm, and London; repeated for information to
                        Bern, Guatemala City, USPOLAD Trieste, and <gloss target="#t_USUN1"
                            >USUN</gloss> in New York.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-07T20:07:00-04:00"
                            >July 7, 1954—8:07 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. In your discretion and in degree commensurate any cooperation you consider
                    shown by Government to which you accredited orally convey appreciation US
                    Government for actions taken or promised regarding prevention of arms shipments
                    to Guatemala and related control flag vessels and general idea cooperation with
                    American republics in meeting threat to peace. State that new Guatemalan
                    Government apparently of such complexion that US able withdraw request for
                    cooperation in arms control.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
